## Existing Context / Notes

From `docs/architecture/apparatus/spider.md`, the "Future Evolution" section mentions:
> **givensSpec templates.** The givensSpec currently holds literal values set at rig spawn time. It will grow to support template expressions (e.g. `${draft.worktreePath}`) that resolve specific values from upstream yields into typed givens…

This is a *different* and future feature (resolving upstream yield fields, not just the top-level `$writ`/`$role`/`$spider.*` variables). The curly brace change in this brief is about syntax sugar for the *current* variable set, not about the future upstream-yield resolution feature. The `${draft.worktreePath}` syntax mentioned in Future Evolution is not part of this brief.

